This paper is primarily focused on data center management and control, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also extensively uses data science tools and techniques, such as predictive modeling and machine learning, which are covered under the categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the feasibility of including the predictive model as the central component of a data-driven autonomic manager, which falls under the category of Control Systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of node failures and their impact on data center operations, which is covered under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
